# ðŸš€ Advanced Suggestions (To Win the Hackathon)
To impress Google judges, you need to show **Multimodality** (Video/Audio/Image) and **Agents** (AI doing things).

### 1. Upgrade "Vaidya" -> "Drishti" (Gemini Vision)
*   **Idea:** Don't just detect disease name. Let the user take a picture of the **entire farm**.
*   **Tech:** Send image to **Gemini 1.5 Flash**.
*   **Prompt:** *"Identify the crop, estimate the growth stage, and spot any signs of nutrient deficiency or water stress in this image. Recommend a fertilizer mix."*
*   **Why it wins:** It moves beyond simple classification to "Agronomic Consulting".

### 2. Upgrade "Lekha Pay" -> "Smart Ledger" (DocAI)
*   **Idea:** Farmers hate typing expenses. Let them take a photo of a **handwritten receipt** (Khata) or fertilizer bill.
*   **Tech:** Use **Gemini 1.5 Pro** to extract: Item Name, Price, Quantity, and Date from the image and **auto-save** it to Supabase/Firestore.
*   **Why it wins:** Real-world utility. Solves the "data entry" friction.

### 3. Upgrade "Market Insights" -> "Mandi Agent" (Function Calling)
*   **Idea:** Instead of dummy charts, let the AI fetch real news.
*   **Tech:** build a simple tool/function `get_onion_prices(district)`.
*   **Gemini Workflow:** User asks *"Should I sell onions today?"* -> Gemini calls API -> Checks price trends -> Advices *"Hold for 2 days, prices in Nashik mandi are rising."*

### 4. Upgrade "Samvaad" -> "Voice-to-Action"
*   **Idea:** The user speaks *"Motor chalu kar do"* (Turn on the motor).
*   **Tech:** **Speech-to-Text** -> **Gemini** extracts intent `{"action": "turn_on", "device": "pump"}` -> App triggers **Bijuka** IoT.
*   **Why it wins:** True "Jarvis for Farmers". No buttons needed.
